FBIS4-60084 "drnes098_s_94004" FBIS-NES-94-098 Daily Report 20 May 1994 Iran Khamene'i Pardons Prisoners To Mark 'Id al-Adha Khamene'i Pardons Prisoners To Mark 'Id al-Adha LD2005095794 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 20 May 94 LD2005095794 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network Persian BFN [Excerpt] On the occasion of the auspicious anniversary of the 'Id al-Adha and 'Id al-Ghadir, His Eminence Ayatollah Khamene'i, the eminent leader of the Islamic revolution and the guardian of the cause of Muslims, pardoned or reduced the sentences of 2,289 persons convicted by Islamic revolution, general, and military courts throughout the country. Ayatollah Yazdi, head of the Judicial Power, requested a pardon or reduction in the sentences of the aforementioned convicted persons and the eminent leader agreed with his request. [passage omitted]
